You are here: Salesforce Help > Docs > Analytics > Report on File Search Activity

Required Editions:
Available in both Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience

User Permissions Needed:
To create or update custom report types: “Manage Custom Report Types”
To run the File Search Activity report: “Run Reports” AND “View All Data” OR “Content Administrator”

Custom report types are the only way to make reports about file search activity available for your users—Salesforce does not provide sample file search activity reports or a standard report folder.

Available File Search Activity Report Fields:
Average Click Rank
Average Number of Results
Duration
Language
Number of Searches
Number of Users
Search Date
Search Terms

See Also: Access to Report Folders, Creating and Editing Folders, Create a Custom Report Type
title: Customizing File Search Activity Reports in Salesforce
